#4339
Forge~
This room is lit only by the intense glow of the forge fire.  The
muscular bladesmith pumps the bellows of the forge, heating the metal
until it glows red.  He then pulls the metal out of the coals with tongs and
then hammers the metal flat, then folds it over on itself, and hammers it
flat again.  When the metal loses its heat, he thrusts it back in the fire
and pumps the bellows again.  This process is repeated scores of times for
each blade produced.  The smith wipes the sweat from his brow with the back
of his hand, and nods at you with a half smile.  The exit from the room is
to the south.
~
